reviewText: This film is one of Jaglom's finest!  The actors and the entire ensemble are just incredible. The chemistry crackles like lightning!

Corey Feldman's return to the big screen after a decade is a cinematic tour-de-force. The M Word holds up on the small screen too. If I had a cellphone, perhaps it would hold up on the smallest screen.

I think Henry Jaglom is a genius and I've seen all of his films and loved practically all of them--but please send Tanna Frederick back to the community theater in Mason City...she's ruining your legacy, Henry.
